Clint Dempsey has also played for New England Revolution, Fulham and Tottenham Hotspur.

Dempsey became the first American player to score a hat-trick in the English Premier League, in the 5–2 win over Newcastle United in January 2012.

Dempsey is of Irish descent on his father's side.

On November 27, 1995, Dempsey lost his then 16-year-old sister Jennifer to a brain aneurysm.

In 2005, Dempsey contributed ten goals and nine assists in 26 games.

Dempsey made his Fulham debut in a 1–1 home draw against Tottenham Hotspur on January 20, 2007.

